{"title_page": "List of fiction works made into feature films (K\u2013R)", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{multiple issues|\n{{Orphan|date=September 2014}}\n{{more citations needed|date=June 2018}}\n}}\n\nThis is a list of fiction works that have been made into [[feature films]]. The title of the work and the year it was published are both followed by the work's author, the title of the film, and the year of the film. If a film has an alternate title based on geographical distribution, the title listed will be that of the widest distribution area.\n{{inc-lit}}\n{{inc-film}}\n{{Compact ToC|num=yes |center=yes|Sec1=Short stories and novellas|seealso=yes|notes=yes}}\n\n== Books ==\n\n=== K ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! width=\"800\"|Fiction work(s) !! width=\"800\"|Film adaptation(s)\n|-\n| ''Kaitei Gunkan'' (1902\u20131907), [[Shunro Oshikawa]]<br />''Kaitei Okoku'' (1931), Shigeru Komatsuzaki\n| ''[[Atragon]]'' (1963)<br />''[[Atragon#Super Atragon|Super Atragon]]'' (1995)\n|-\n| ''Kami no Tsuki'' (2012), [[Mitsuyo Kakuta]]\n| ''[[Pale Moon (film)|Pale Moon]]'' (2014)\n|-\n| ''Kenka erejii'' (1963), Takashi Suzuki\n| ''[[Fighting Elegy]]'' (1966)\n|-\n| ''[[The Keys of the Kingdom]]'' (1941), [[A. J. Cronin]]\n| ''[[The Keys of the Kingdom (film)|The Keys of the Kingdom]]'' (1944)\n|-\n| ''Khamphiphaksa'' (''The Judgment'') (1981), [[Chart Korbjitti]]\n| ''[[Ai-Fak]]'' (2004)\n|-\n| ''[[Kidnapped (novel)|Kidnapped]]'' (1886), [[Robert Louis Stevenson]]\n| ''[[Kidnapped (1938 film)|Kidnapped]]'' (1938)<br />''[[Kidnapped (1960 film)|Kidnapped]]'' (1960)<br />''[[Kidnapped (1971 film)|Kidnapped]]'' (1971)<br />''[[Kidnapped (1995 film)|Kidnapped]]'' (1995)\n|-\n| ''[[The King's Damosel]]'' (1976), [[Vera Chapman]]\n| ''[[Quest for Camelot]]'' (1998)\n|-\n| ''Kings Row'' (1940), [[Henry Bellamann]]\n| ''[[Kings Row]]'' (1942), directed by Sam Wood\n|-\n| ''[[King Solomon's Mines]]'' (1885), Sir [[H. Rider Haggard]]\n| ''[[King Solomon's