ert|Les Mis\u00e9rables \u2013 The Dream Cast in Concert]]'' (1995)<br />''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (1998 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]'' (1998)<br />''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables#Adaptations - Film and television - Les Mis\u00e9rables (2000 TV miniseries)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]'' (2000) (TV) (mini) <small>(Later re-adapted as an edited-down television film version the same year and dubbed into English)</small><br />''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables#Adaptations - Film and television - Les Mis\u00e9rables - 25th Anniversary Live from the O2 (2010)|Les Mis\u00e9rables - 25th Anniversary Live from the O2]]'' (2010)<br />''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables#Adaptations - Film and television - Les Mis\u00e9rables (2011 television play)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]'' (2011) (TV)<br />''[[Les Mis\u00e9rables (2012 film)|Les Mis\u00e9rables]]'' (2012)\n|-\n| ''[[Misery (novel)|Misery]]'' (1987), [[Stephen King]]\n| ''[[Misery (film)|Misery]]'' (1990)\n|-\n| ''[[Miss Lonelyhearts]]'' (1933), [[Nathanael West]]\n| ''[[Miss Lonelyhearts#Film, TV or theatrical adaptations \u2013 1933 film|Advice to the Lovelorn]]'' (1933)<br />''[[Lonelyhearts]]'' (1958)<br />''[[Miss Lonelyhearts#Film, TV or theatrical adaptations \u2013 1983 film|Miss Lonelyhearts]]'' (1983) (TV)\n|-\n| ''[[Moby-Dick]]'' (1851), [[Herman Melville]]\n| ''[[The Sea Beast]]'' (1926)<br/>''[[Moby Dick (1956 film)|Moby Dick]]'' (1956)<br />''[[Tom and Jerry]] in: [[Dicky Moe]]'' (1962)<br />''[[Moby Dick (1978 film)|Moby Dick]]'' (1978)<br />''[[Dot and the Whale]]'' (1986)<br />''[[Adaptations of Moby-Dick#Moby Dick, a 1998 television film starring Patrick Stewart as Ahab and Gregory Peck as Father Mapple (a Golden Globe-winning performance)|Moby Dick]]'' (1998) (TV)<br />''[[Adaptations of Moby-Dick#In 1999, a 25-minute paint-on-glass-animated adaptation was made by the Russian studio Man and Time, directed by Natalya Orlova. It was made for the British market, and so was in English. Rod Steiger was the voice of Captain Ahab. The film came in third plac