0, 2014.</ref>\n\n== Activities ==\nIn 2017, the school conducted a youth football camp in partnership with five-time Bundesliga champion Borussia Monchengladbach.<ref>{{cite news |title=Football: Borussia Monchengladbach to conduct youth camp in Singapore in June |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/sport/football/football-borussia-monchengladbach-to-conduct-youth-camp-in-singapore-in-june |accessdate=19 April 2019 |work=The Straits Times |agency=The Straits Times |publisher=The Straits Times |date=5 June 2017 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n==Campus==\nThe new purpose build GESS campus, opened at Dairy Farm Lane in August 2018. The building costs were about $135 million and the campus spans across a 30,580 sqm site.\n=== Facilities ===\n\n* Olympic-size swimming pool, \n* football field, \n* cooking studio, \n* 400-seat auditorium, \n* black box theatre, \n* 3 Libraries (pre-school, primary school and secondary school) \n* design technology studio that aims to promote engineering among 13-and 14-year-olds.<ref>{{cite news |title=International school opens facilities to local groups |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/education/international-school-opens-facilities-to-local-groups |accessdate=19 April 2019 |work=The Straits Times |agency=The Straits Times |publisher=The Straits Times |date=14 September 2018 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n=== Green Features ===\nAlso, the building facade is shrouded in vertical greenery, and features a rainwater-harvesting system and rain garden to irrigate plants and filter rainwater runoff.<ref>{{cite news |title=Green features for new German school |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/education/green-features-for-new-german-school |accessdate=19 April 2019 |work=The Straits Times |agency=The Straits Times |publisher=The Straits Times |date=10 May 2016 |language=en}}</ref> It also has two solar panels built on top of block F.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{portal|Germany|Singapore|Schools}}\n* {{Official website|https://www.gess.sg/}}\n\n{{International schools in Singapore}}\n{{German schools in Asia}}\n\n[[Category:German international schools|Singapore]]\n[[Category:International schools in Singapore]]\n[[Category:Germany\u2013Singapore relations]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1971]]\n", "name_user": "2401:7400:c802:b4f9:1c02:110:1027:d2d3", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/German_European_School_Singapore"}
